Large amounts: Transactions of a large amount are more likely to be fraudulent, as fraudsters may try to steal large amounts of money at once.
Transactions with a large change in balance: Transactions with a large change in balance, either positive or negative, may be more likely to be fraudulent. This is because fraudsters may try to quickly transfer money out of an account before they are detected.
Transactions with a balance that is close to zero: Transactions with a balance that is close to zero may be more likely to be fraudulent, as fraudsters may try to empty out accounts before they are detected.
